related_items.title: Benito Mussolini in der Hauptstadt der Bewegung, MCMXXXVII
description: 1 album (88 photographic prints, 8 leaves of text) ; 48 x 40 cm. (album) | Pictures of soldiers, children, Hitler Youth, SA troups and other welcoming committees greeting Mussolini's special train on his way to Munich, Germany in September 1937 with stops along the way in many small towns. Pictures include Hitler meeting Mussolini at the train station, Italian photographers, parade in Munich, Hitler and Mussolini in open car, driving through the city, in the Braunes Haus in Munich, wreath-laying ceremonies, Mussolini with various Nazi officials, and parade in front of Königsplatz in Munich.
